{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KhrtV77LZzzQ1rTx5eJ8Na","type":"tool_result","content":"{\"body\":\"PR for issue: #944\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n- **Root cause**: the fire-and-forget `/api/trial/init` fetch in the OAuth callback page used `keepalive: false` (browser default), so the browser aborted the in-flight request when `window.location.replace()` navigated away. This regressed #922 because in-cluster Redis (post-#760) is slower than Vercel KV was, making the race condition consistently triggered in production.\\n- **Fix 1 (primary)**: Add `keepalive: true` to the trial init fetch in `auth/callback/page.tsx` so the browser completes the request even after page navigation.\\n- **Fix 2 (fallback)**: Auto-initialize the trial in `POST /api/trial/status` when no record exists — idempotent defense-in-depth that also satisfies the \\\"canceled Stripe customers can start a trial\\\" AC (no Stripe status is checked in the trial flow).\\n\\n## Files Changed\\n\\n- `development/frontend/src/app/ledger/auth/callback/page.tsx` — add `keepalive: true`\\n- `development/frontend/src/app/api/trial/status/route.ts` — auto-init on missing trial\\n- `development/frontend/src/__tests__/trial/trial-status-route.test.ts` — 14 new integration tests\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] 14 new Vitest tests for `POST /api/trial/status` (auto-init, canceled Stripe AC, active/expired/converted, auth/validation/rate-limit)\\n- [x] All 785 Vitest tests pass (`npx vitest run`)\\n- [x] `tsc --noEmit` clean (`quality/scripts/verify.sh --step tsc`)\\n- [ ] Manual: sign in with Google, verify `/api/trial/status` returns `{status:\\\"active\\\", remainingDays:30}`\\n- [ ] Manual: sign in with canceled Stripe customer, verify trial starts\\n\\nFixes #944\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\"number\":947,\"title\":\"Issue #944 - fix: resolve trial not starting on sign-in\"}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f0c11e7-f1f2-45f1-b28f-b520f037c3ce","uuid":"d05cd37e-e206-4180-9667-46a852bcd72c","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"{\"body\":\"PR for issue: #944\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n- **Root cause**: the fire-and-forget `/api/trial/init` fetch in the OAuth callback page used `keepalive: false` (browser default), so the browser aborted the in-flight request when `window.location.replace()` navigated away. This regressed #922 because in-cluster Redis (post-#760) is slower than Vercel KV was, making the race condition consistently triggered in production.\\n- **Fix 1 (primary)**: Add `keepalive: true` to the trial init fetch in `auth/callback/page.tsx` so the browser completes the request even after page navigation.\\n- **Fix 2 (fallback)**: Auto-initialize the trial in `POST /api/trial/status` when no record exists — idempotent defense-in-depth that also satisfies the \\\"canceled Stripe customers can start a trial\\\" AC (no Stripe status is checked in the trial flow).\\n\\n## Files Changed\\n\\n- `development/frontend/src/app/ledger/auth/callback/page.tsx` — add `keepalive: true`\\n- `development/frontend/src/app/api/trial/status/route.ts` — auto-init on missing trial\\n- `development/frontend/src/__tests__/trial/trial-status-route.test.ts` — 14 new integration tests\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] 14 new Vitest tests for `POST /api/trial/status` (auto-init, canceled Stripe AC, active/expired/converted, auth/validation/rate-limit)\\n- [x] All 785 Vitest tests pass (`npx vitest run`)\\n- [x] `tsc --noEmit` clean (`quality/scripts/verify.sh --step tsc`)\\n- [ ] Manual: sign in with Google, verify `/api/trial/status` returns `{status:\\\"active\\\", remainingDays:30}`\\n- [ ] Manual: sign in with canceled Stripe customer, verify trial starts\\n\\nFixes #944\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\"number\":947,\"title\":\"Issue #944 - fix: resolve trial not starting on sign-in\"}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
